cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper combines two popular approaches in natural language processing: distributional models and deep learning embeddings. The focus on word relatedness judgment suggests a strong connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of deep learning embeddings and the comparison to one-hot vectors suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of distributional models also suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
